The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks to improve the resolution of optical microscopy images. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves image processing and analysis. The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the training of a neural network, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for this approach to be used in the design of computational imagers, which could fall under the category of robotics (cs.RO).
